Learn all 48 ceremonial (geographic) Counties of England: from Northumberland to Cornwall, from Greater Manchester to Greater London.
Several quiz modes to test your knowledge:
1) Maps of 48 ceremonial counties;
2) County towns (= modern administrative centers);
3) 47 Flags of the counties (Bristol does not have a city/county flag);
4) Multiple-choice questions combining all above topics;
5) Time game: give as many correct answers as you can in 1 minute.

Earn all stars and become an expert in the geography of England - a constituent country of the United Kingdom covering the central and southern part of the island of Great Britain. 

Before taking quizzes, you may like to study English counties and regions using Flashcards.
I heartily recommend this app to everyone interested in the UK and British geography and history.
